*   November 1925 – [Walter Guinness](/Walter_Guinness) succeeded [E. F. L. Wood](/E._F._L._Wood) as [Minister of Agriculture](/Minister_of_Agriculture,_Fisheries_and_Food).
*   July 1926 – The office of [Secretary of Scotland](/Secretary_of_Scotland) was elevated to the more senior position of [Secretary of State for Scotland](/Secretary_of_State_for_Scotland).
*   October 1927 – [Lord Cushendun](/Lord_Cushendun) succeeded [Lord Cecil of Chelwood](/Lord_Cecil_of_Chelwood) as [Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster](/Chancellor_of_the_Duchy_of_Lancaster).
*   March 1928 – [Lord Hailsham](/Douglas_Hogg,_1st_Viscount_Hailsham) (formerly Douglas Hogg) succeeded [Lord Cave](/Lord_Cave) as [Lord Chancellor](/Lord_Chancellor). Hailsham's successor as [Attorney-General](/Attorney-General) was not a member of the Cabinet.
